Cassino

In Sept., 1943 the Allies have landed in Sicily. They hope to reach Rome within half a year. At the Gustav Line, stretching from coast to coast across Southern Italy, their schedule fails. The center of combat operations is the Monte Cassino. This scenario deals with the first Allied assault.

